wfivRouteBroadcastRouteTimer.name: wfivRouteBroadcastRouteTimer
wfivRouteBroadcastRouteTimer.description: 'This value determines the maximum time allowed between Routing updates on Ethernet circuits. When this timer expires before a routing update occurs, a routing update is forced. With a standard calculation, Routing also uses this timer to enforce a minimum delay between routing updates. Seconds is a decimal integer in the range 1-65535.'

wfivRouteRoutingVers.name: wfivRouteRoutingVers
wfivRouteRoutingVers.description: 'This read-only parameter identifies the executor node's Routing version number. The format is the same as for the Network Management version number.'

wfivRouteMaxAddr.name: wfivRouteMaxAddr
wfivRouteMaxAddr.description: 'This value represents the largest node number and, therefore, number of nodes that can be known about by the executor node's home area. The number is an integer in the range 1-1023.'

wfivRouteMaxBdcastNonRouters.name: wfivRouteMaxBdcastNonRouters
wfivRouteMaxBdcastNonRouters.description: 'This value represents the maximum total number of nonrouters the executor node can have on its broadcast circuits for one slot. The number is an integer in the range 0-1023.'

wfivRouteMaxBdcastRouters.name: wfivRouteMaxBdcastRouters
wfivRouteMaxBdcastRouters.description: 'This value represents the maximum total number of routers the executor node can have on its broadcast circuits for one slot. The number is an integer in the range 0-1023.'

wfivRouteMaxCircuits.name: wfivRouteMaxCircuits
wfivRouteMaxCircuits.description: 'This value represents the maximum number of Routing circuits that the executor node can know about. The number is decimal in the range 1-65535. Wellfleet limits this to 1024'

wfivRouteMaxCost.name: wfivRouteMaxCost
wfivRouteMaxCost.description: 'This value represents the maximum total path cost allowed from the executor to any node within an area. The path cost is the sum of the circuit costs along a path between two nodes. This parameter defines the point where the executor node's Routing decision algorithm declares another node unreachable because the cost of the least costly path to the other node is excessive. For correct operation, this parameter must not be less than the maximum path cost of the network. The MAXIMUM COST number is decimal in the range 1-1022.'

wfivRouteMaxHops.name: wfivRouteMaxHops
wfivRouteMaxHops.description: 'This value represents the maximum number of routing hops allowable from the executor to any other reachable node within an area. (A hop is the logical distance over a circuit between two adjacent nodes.) This parameter defines the point where the executor node's Routing decision algorithm declares another node unreachable because the length of the shortest path between the two nodes is too long. For correct operation, this parameter must not be less than the network diameter. (The network diameter is the reachability distance between the two nodes of the network having the greatest reachability distance, where reachability distance is the length the shortest path between a given pair of nodes.) The MAXIMUM HOPS number is decimal in the range 1-30.'

wfivRouteMaxVisits.name: wfivRouteMaxVisits
wfivRouteMaxVisits.description: 'This value represents the maximum number of nodes a message coming into the executor node can have visited. If the message is not for this node and the MAXIMUM VISITS number is exceeded, the message is discarded. The MAXIMUM VISITS parameter defines the point where the packet lifetime control algorithm discards a packet that has traversed too many nodes. For correct operation, this parameter must not be less than the maximum path length of the network. (The maximum path length is the routing distance between the two nodes of the network having the greatest routing distance, where routing distance is the length of the least costly path between a given pair of nodes.) The MAXIMUM VISITS number is decimal in the range MAXIMUM HOPS to 63.'

wfivRouteAreaMaxCost.name: wfivRouteAreaMaxCost
wfivRouteAreaMaxCost.description: 'This value represents the maximum total path cost allowed from the executor to any other level 2 routing node. The AREA MAXIMUM COST number is decimal in the range 1-1022. This parameter is only applicable if the executor node is of type AREA.'

wfivRouteAreaMaxHops.name: wfivRouteAreaMaxHops
wfivRouteAreaMaxHops.description: 'This value represents the maximum number of routing hops allowable from the executor to any other level 2 routing node. The AREA MAXIMUM HOPS number is decimal in the range 1-30.This parameter is only applicable if the executor node is of type AREA.'

wfivRouteMaxArea.name: wfivRouteMaxArea
wfivRouteMaxArea.description: 'This value represents the largest area number and, therefore, number of areas that can be known about by the executor node's Routing. This parameter is only applicable if the executor node is of type AREA. The number is an integer in the range 1-63.'

wfivRouteType.name: wfivRouteType
wfivRouteType.description: 'This parameter indicates the type of the executor node. The node-type is one of the following: ROUTING III NONROUTING III ROUTING IV NONROUTING IV AREA A routing node has full routing capability. A nonrouting node contains a subset of the Routing modules. The III and IV indicate the DNA phase of the node. Nonrouting nodes can deliver and receive packets to and from any node, but cannot route packets from other nodes through to other nodes. An area node routes between areas. Refer to the Routing specification for details. For adjacent nodes, this is a read-only parameter that indicates the type of the reachable adjacent node. NOTE: The ROUTING III and NONROUTING III values are incremented by one compared to the standard DECnet values in order to maintain compliance with RFC 1155)'

wfivCircuitRouterPri.name: wfivCircuitRouterPri

NOTE: The ROUTING III and NONROUTING III values are incremented by one compared to the standard DECnet values in order to maintain compliance with RFC 1155) ROUTING III (1), NONROUTING III (2), AREA (3), ROUTING IV (4), NONROUTING IV (5)'

wfivAdjState.name: wfivAdjState
wfivAdjState.description: 'This value indicates the state of a router adjacency. On adjacencies over a circuit of type (wfivCircuitCommonType) Ethernet, CI, or FDDI, with an adjacent node of type (wfivAdjType) ROUTING IV or AREA, this variable is the state of the Ethernet Initialization Layer for this adjacency, and can have values INITIALIZING or UP. (See Section 9.1.1 of DECnet Phase IV Routing Layer Functional Specification.) On adjacencies over a circuit of type (wfivCircuitCommonType) Ethernet, CI, or FDDI, with an adjacent node of type (wfivAdjType) NONROUTING IV, this varaible will always take on the value UP. On adjacencies over a circuit of type (wfivCircuitCommonType) DDCMP POINT, DDCMP CONTROL, DDCMP TRIBUTARY, DDCMP DMC, or X.25, this variable is the state of the Routing Layer Initialization Circuit State. (See section 7.3, ibid.) It can have values between RUN and HALT. On adjacencies over a circuit of type (wfivCircuitCommonType) OTHER, this variable may be used in a manner consistent with the Initialization Layer used on that circuit. INITIALIZING (1), -- Ethernet one-way UP (2), -- Ethernet two-way RUN (3), -- The eight DDCMP/X.25 states CIRCUIT REJECTED (4), DATA LINK START (5), ROUTING LAYER INITIALIZE (6), ROUTING LAYER VERIFY (7), ROUTING LAYER COMPLETE (8), OFF (9), HALT (10)'

wfFDDISmtConnectionPolicy.name: wfFDDISmtConnectionPolicy
wfFDDISmtConnectionPolicy.description: A value that indicates the connection policies enforced at the station. A station sets the corresponding policy for each of the connection types that it rejects. The letter designations, X and Y, in the 'rejectX-Y' names have the following significance: X represents the PC-Type of the local PORT and Y represents a PC-Neighbor in the evaluation of Connection-Policy (PC-Type, PC- Neighbor) that is done to determine the setting of T-Val(3) in the PC-Signaling sequence. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each of the connection policies currently enforced on the node, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Policy Power rejectA-A 0 rejectA-B 1 rejectA-S 2 rejectA-M 3 rejectB-A 4 rejectB-B 5 rejectB-S 6 rejectB-M 7 rejectS-A 8 rejectS-B 9 rejectS-S 10 rejectS-M 11 rejectM-A 12 rejectM-B 13 rejectM-S 14 rejectM-M 15

wfIpBaseCreate.name: wfIpBaseCreate
wfIpBaseCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete IP.

wfIpBaseEnable.name: wfIpBaseEnable
wfIpBaseEnable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable IP.

wfIpBaseState.name: wfIpBaseState
wfIpBaseState.description: The current state of the entire IP.

wfIpBaseForwarding.name: wfIpBaseForwarding
wfIpBaseForwarding.description: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IP gateway in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IP gateways forward datagrams. IP hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host). Note that for some managed nodes, this object may take on only a subset of the values possible. Accordingly, it is appropriate for an agent to return a `badValue' response if a management station attempts to change this object to an inappropriate value.

wfIpBaseDefaultTTL.name: wfIpBaseDefaultTTL
wfIpBaseDefaultTTL.description: The default value inserted into the Time-To-Live field of the IP header of datagrams originated at this entity, whenever a TTL value is not supplied by the transport layer protocol.

wfIpBaseRipDiameter.name: wfIpBaseRipDiameter
wfIpBaseRipDiameter.description: The Diameter of the RIP network. 1 less than 'infinity'

wfIpBaseRtEntryTable.name: wfIpBaseRtEntryTable
wfIpBaseRtEntryTable.description: The list of elements in IP's routing table

wfIpBaseRouteDest.name: wfIpBaseRouteDest
wfIpBaseRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

wfIpBaseRouteIfIndex.name: wfIpBaseRouteIfIndex
wfIpBaseRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric1.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric1
wfIpBaseRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric2.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric2
wfIpBaseRouteMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric3.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric3
wfIpBaseRouteMetric3.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric4.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric4
wfIpBaseRouteMetric4.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteNextHop.name: wfIpBaseRouteNextHop
wfIpBaseRouteNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface.)

wfIpBaseRouteType.name: wfIpBaseRouteType
wfIpBaseRouteType.description: The type of route. Note that the values direct(3) and indirect(4) refer to the notion of direct and indirect routing in the IP architecture. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipRouteTable object. That is, it effectively dissasociates the destination identified with said entry from the route identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. nagement stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipRouteType object.

wfIpBaseRouteProto.name: wfIpBaseRouteProto
wfIpBaseRouteProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

wfIpBaseRouteAge.name: wfIpBaseRouteAge
wfIpBaseRouteAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

wfIpBaseRouteMask.name: wfIpBaseRouteMask
wfIpBaseRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the ipRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the ipRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent ipRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the ipRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric5.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric5
wfIpBaseRouteMetric5.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteInfo.name: wfIpBaseRouteInfo
wfIpBaseRouteInfo.description: A user-defined string which describes this Route entry

wfIpBaseHostEntryTable.name: wfIpBaseHostEntryTable
wfIpBaseHostEntryTable.description: The list of elements in IP's host table

wfIpBaseHostEntry.name: wfIpBaseHostEntry
wfIpBaseHostEntry.description: A description of a resolved host

wfIpBaseNetToMediaIfIndex.name: wfIpBaseNetToMediaIfIndex
wfIpBaseNetToMediaIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfIpBaseNetToMediaNetAddress.name: wfIpBaseNetToMediaNetAddress
wfIpBaseNetToMediaNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media-dependent `physical' address.

wfIpBaseNetToMediaType.name: wfIpBaseNetToMediaType
wfIpBaseNetToMediaType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipNetToMediaTable. That is, it effectively dissasociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipNetToMediaType object.

wfIpInterfaceTable.name: wfIpInterfaceTable
wfIpInterfaceTable.description: The list of configured IP interface

wfIpInterfaceCreate.name: wfIpInterfaceCreate
wfIpInterfaceCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete an IP interface.

wfIpInterfaceEnable.name: wfIpInterfaceEnable
wfIpInterfaceEnable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable an IP interface.

wfIpInterfaceState.name: wfIpInterfaceState
wfIpInterfaceState.description: INvalid indicates an error in processing the cfg record

wfIpInterfaceAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceAddr
wfIpInterfaceAddr.description: The IP Address to which this entry's addressing information pertains

wfIpInterfaceCircuit.name: wfIpInterfaceCircuit
wfIpInterfaceCircuit.description: The Circuit Number that this interface runs over

wfIpInterfaceMask.name: wfIpInterfaceMask
wfIpInterfaceMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

wfIpInterfaceCost.name: wfIpInterfaceCost
wfIpInterfaceCost.description: The Cost metric associated with the IP Address of this entry

wfIpInterfaceCfgBcastAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceCfgBcastAddr
wfIpInterfaceCfgBcastAddr.description: The user can specifcy a broadcast address for a NWIF

wfIpInterfaceBcastAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceBcastAddr
wfIpInterfaceBcastAddr.description: The value of the broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface. This is value used by the software

wfIpInterfaceMTUDiscovery.name: wfIpInterfaceMTUDiscovery
wfIpInterfaceMTUDiscovery.description: Whether MTU discovery option is on/off

wfIpInterfaceAMR.name: wfIpInterfaceAMR
wfIpInterfaceAMR.description: Whether Address Mask Reply is ON/OFF

wfIpInterfaceASB.name: wfIpInterfaceASB
wfIpInterfaceASB.description: Whether All-Subnet Broadcasts Are excepted and Sent out this NWIF

wfIpInterfaceAddressResolutionType.name: wfIpInterfaceAddressResolutionType
wfIpInterfaceAddressResolutionType.description: Indicates which Address Resolution Type to use

wfIpInterfaceProxy.name: wfIpInterfaceProxy
wfIpInterfaceProxy.description: Indicates Whether Proxy is on this Interface or not

wfIpInterfaceHostCache.name: wfIpInterfaceHostCache
wfIpInterfaceHostCache.description: Whether the Host Cache (Address Aging) is on or not. A Range of discrete values is specified as well as a value meaning don't age

wfIpInterfaceUdpXsumOn.name: wfIpInterfaceUdpXsumOn
wfIpInterfaceUdpXsumOn.description: Whether to turn UDP checksum verification on for UDP packets recieved and transmitted by this router

wfIpInterfaceCfgMacAddress.name: wfIpInterfaceCfgMacAddress
wfIpInterfaceCfgMacAddress.description: The desired mac set by the user

wfIpInterfaceMacAddress.name: wfIpInterfaceMacAddress
wfIpInterfaceMacAddress.description: The MAC Address for this Interface- actual one used

wfIpInterfaceReasmMaxSize.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmMaxSize
wfIpInterfaceReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagrams received on this interface.

wfIpInterfaceMaxInfo.name: wfIpInterfaceMaxInfo
wfIpInterfaceMaxInfo.description: The maximum size of the INFO (non-MAC) field that this port will receive or transmit.

wfIpInterfaceInReceives.name: wfIpInterfaceInReceives
wfIpInterfaceInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.

wfIpInterfaceInHdrErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceInHdrErrors
wfIpInterfaceInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

wfIpInterfaceInAddrErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceInAddrErrors
wfIpInterfaceInAddrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP Gateways and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

wfIpInterfaceForwDatagrams.name: wfIpInterfaceForwDatagrams
wfIpInterfaceForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination. In entities which do not act as IP Gateways, this counter will include only those packets which were Source-Routed via this entity, and the Source- Route option processing was successful.

wfIpInterfaceInUnknownProtos.name: wfIpInterfaceInUnknownProtos
wfIpInterfaceInUnknownProtos.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

wfIpInterfaceInDiscards.name: wfIpInterfaceInDiscards
wfIpInterfaceInDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

wfIpInterfaceInDelivers.name: wfIpInterfaceInDelivers
wfIpInterfaceInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).

wfIpInterfaceOutRequests.name: wfIpInterfaceOutRequests
wfIpInterfaceOutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

wfIpInterfaceOutDiscards.name: wfIpInterfaceOutDiscards
wfIpInterfaceOutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams if any such packets met this (discretionary) discard criterion.

wfIpInterfaceOutNoRoutes.name: wfIpInterfaceOutNoRoutes
wfIpInterfaceOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in ipForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion. Note that this includes any datagarms which a host cannot route because all of its default gateways are down.

wfIpInterfaceReasmTimeout.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmTimeout
wfIpInterfaceReasmTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds which received fragments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceReasmReqds.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmReqds
wfIpInterfaceReasmReqds.description: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceReasmOKs.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmOKs
wfIpInterfaceReasmOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams successfully reassembled.

wfIpInterfaceReasmFails.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmFails
wfIpInterfaceReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re- assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

wfIpInterfaceFragOKs.name: wfIpInterfaceFragOKs
wfIpInterfaceFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceFragFails.name: wfIpInterfaceFragFails
wfIpInterfaceFragFails.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be, e.g., because their Don't Fragment flag was set.

wfIpInterfaceFragCreates.name: wfIpInterfaceFragCreates
wfIpInterfaceFragCreates.description: The number of IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInMsgs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInMsgs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which includes all those counted by wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInDestUnreachs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInDestUnreachs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimeExcds.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimeExcds
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInParmProbs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInParmProbs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInSrcQuenchs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInSrcQuenchs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRedirects.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRedirects
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchos.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchos
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchoReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchoReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestamps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestamps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestampReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestampReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMasks.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMasks
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMaskReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMaskReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutMsgs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutMsgs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutErrors
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations there may be no types of error which contribute to this counter's value.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutDestUnreachs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutDestUnreachs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimeExcds.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimeExcds
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutParmProbs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutParmProbs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutSrcQuenchs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRedirects.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRedirects
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages sent. For a host, this object will always be zero, since hosts do not send redirects.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchos.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchos
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchoReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchoReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestamps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestamps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestampReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestampReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMasks.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMasks
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMaskReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceTrEndStation.description: Use Source Routing over token ring selection. Only applies if pam type is TRING.

wfIpInterfaceRedirect.name: wfIpInterfaceRedirect
wfIpInterfaceRedirect.description: Indicates Whether we're sending out redirects on this Interface or not

wfIpInterfaceEnetArpEncaps.name: wfIpInterfaceEnetArpEncaps
wfIpInterfaceEnetArpEncaps.description: The data link encapsulation type to use for ARP packets if the the media is ethernet.

wfIpSrIpNetMask.name: wfIpSrIpNetMask

wfIpSrCost.name: wfIpSrCost

wfIpSrIpAddressRt.name: wfIpSrIpAddressRt
wfIpSrIpAddressRt.description: The Route Identifier Which numbered route this is to be

wfIpSrValid.name: wfIpSrValid
wfIpSrValid.description: Whether this Static Route is valid or not

wfIpAdjacentHostTable.name: wfIpAdjacentHostTable
wfIpAdjacentHostTable.description: The list of Adjacent Hosts (static IP-Mac resolutions)

wfIpAdjacentHostEntry.name: wfIpAdjacentHostEntry
wfIpAdjacentHostEntry.description: A description of an adjacent host

wfIpAdjHostMacAddr.description: The LAN Address for this HOST

wfIpAdjHostEncaps.name: wfIpAdjHostEncaps
wfIpAdjHostEncaps.description: The encapsulation type of this entry

wfIpAdjHostValid.name: wfIpAdjHostValid
wfIpAdjHostValid.description: Whether the record passed validation or not

wfIpTrafficFilterCreate.name: wfIpTrafficFilterCreate
wfIpTrafficFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfIpTrafficFilterEnable.name: wfIpTrafficFilterEnable
wfIpTrafficFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfIpTrafficFilterStatus.name: wfIpTrafficFilterStatus
wfIpTrafficFilterStatus.description: Defines the current status of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfIpTrafficFilterCircuit.name: wfIpTrafficFilterCircuit
wfIpTrafficFilterCircuit.description: The ID of the Circuit to which the filter is applied.

wfRipIntfTable.name: wfRipIntfTable

wfRipIntfEntry.name: wfRipIntfEntry
wfRipIntfEntry.description: A description of a RIP interface

wfRipInterfaceCreate.name: wfRipInterfaceCreate
wfRipInterfaceCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete an RIP Interface instance.

wfRipInterfaceEnable.name: wfRipInterfaceEnable
wfRipInterfaceEnable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable a RIP interface.

wfRipInterfaceState.name: wfRipInterfaceState
wfRipInterfaceState.description: The current state of RIP on this interface.

wfRipInterfaceIndex.name: wfRipInterfaceIndex
wfRipInterfaceIndex.description: The IP interface to run RIP on.

wfRipInterfaceListen.name: wfRipInterfaceListen
wfRipInterfaceListen.description: Whether to listen to RIP packets

wfRipInterfaceDefaultRouteSupply.name: wfRipInterfaceDefaultRouteSupply
wfRipInterfaceDefaultRouteSupply.description: Transmit the default route, 0.0.0.0, in RIP packets.

wfRipInterfaceDefaultRouteListen.name: wfRipInterfaceDefaultRouteListen
wfRipInterfaceDefaultRouteListen.description: Receive the default route, 0.0.0.0, in RIP packets.

wfRipInterfacePoisonedReversed.name: wfRipInterfacePoisonedReversed
wfRipInterfacePoisonedReversed.description: Specifies how the router advertises routes it has learned from a neighboring router in periodic updates subsequently sent to the neighbor. If 'Poisoned', the node implements poisoned reverse. The router now advertises routes learned from a neighbor in RIP updates subsequently sent to that neighbor with a hop count of wfRipBaseRipNetworkDiameter plus 1, (thus declaring the destination unreachable). If 'Split', the router implements a split-horizon, and omits routes learned from a neighbor in RIP updates subsequently sent to that neighbor. If 'Actual', the learned cost of the route is advertised.

wfOspfAreaBdrRtrStatus.name: wfOspfAreaBdrRtrStatus
wfOspfAreaBdrRtrStatus.description: 'A flag to note whether this router is an area border router.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 3 Splitting the AS into Areas'

wfOspfASBdrRtrStatus.name: wfOspfASBdrRtrStatus
wfOspfASBdrRtrStatus.description: 'A flag to note whether this router is an Autonomous System border router.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 3.3 Classification of routers'

wfOspfTOSSupport.name: wfOspfTOSSupport
wfOspfTOSSupport.description: 'The router's support for type-of-service routing.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix F.1.2 Optional TOS support'

wfOspfSpfHoldDown.name: wfOspfSpfHoldDown
wfOspfSpfHoldDown.description: Hold Down Timer for the SPF. The SPF will run at most once per hold down timer value. A value of 0 means no hold down.

wfOspfSlotMask.name: wfOspfSlotMask
wfOspfSlotMask.description: Slot mask for which slots OSPF is eligible to run on. The LSBit represents slot 1, the next least significant bit represents slot 2, and so on... Slots can be 1-14.

wfOspfAreaTable.name: wfOspfAreaTable
wfOspfAreaTable.description: -- The OSPF Area Data Structure contains information -- regarding the various areas. The interfaces and -- virtual links are configured as part of these areas. -- Area 0.0.0.0, by definition, is the Backbone Area 'Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Structure'

wfOspfAreaEntry.name: wfOspfAreaEntry
wfOspfAreaEntry.description: 'Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.'

wfOspfAreaDelete.name: wfOspfAreaDelete
wfOspfAreaDelete.description: This value determines if the OSPF router is configured with this area.

wfOspfAreaDisable.name: wfOspfAreaDisable
wfOspfAreaDisable.description: This value indicates the state of this area on the OSPF router.

wfOspfAreaState.name: wfOspfAreaState
wfOspfAreaState.description: This value indicates the state of the OSPF Area.

wfOspfAreaId.name: wfOspfAreaId
wfOspfAreaId.description: 'A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfAuthType.name: wfOspfAuthType
wfOspfAuthType.description: 'The authentication type specified for an area. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally on a per Area basis.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix E Authentication' -- none (0), -- simplePassword (1) -- reserved for future specification (2..255) -- reserved for AS specific values (> 255)

wfOspfImportASExtern.name: wfOspfImportASExtern
wfOspfImportASExtern.description: 'The area's support for importing AS external link- state advertisements.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfStubMetric.name: wfOspfStubMetric
wfOspfStubMetric.description: 'The metric value applied at the indicated type of service. By default, this equals the least metric at the type of service among the interfaces to other areas.'

wfOspfImportSum.name: wfOspfImportSum
wfOspfImportSum.description: 'The area's support for importing Summary advertisements into a stub area. This variable should not be set unless wfOspfImportASExtern is set to FALSE'

wfOspfLsdbTable.name: wfOspfLsdbTable
wfOspfLsdbTable.description: -- OSPF Link State Database -- The Link State Database contains the Link State -- Advertisements from throughout the areas that the -- device is attached to. 'The OSPF Process's Links State Database.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Advertisements'

wfOspfLsdbAreaId.name: wfOspfLsdbAreaId
wfOspfLsdbAreaId.description: 'The 32 bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfLsdbType.name: wfOspfLsdbType
wfOspfLsdbType.description: 'The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header' stubLink (0), routerLink (1), networkLink (2), summaryLink (3), asSummaryLink (4), asExternalLink (5)

wfOspfLsdbLSID.name: wfOspfLsdbLSID
wfOspfLsdbLSID.description: 'The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4 Link State ID'

wfOspfLsdbRouterId.name: wfOspfLsdbRouterId
wfOspfLsdbRouterId.description: 'The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters'

wfOspfLsdbSequence.name: wfOspfLsdbSequence
wfOspfLsdbSequence.description: -- Note that the OSPF Sequence Number is a 32 bit signed -- integer. It starts with the value '80000001'h, -- or -'7FFFFFFF'h, and increments until '7FFFFFFF'h -- Thus, a typical sequence number will be very negative. 'The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number'

wfOspfLsdbAge.name: wfOspfLsdbAge
wfOspfLsdbAge.description: 'This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.' (OSPF_LSDBMINAGE = 0) REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.1 LS age'

wfOspfLsdbChecksum.name: wfOspfLsdbChecksum
wfOspfLsdbChecksum.description: 'This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.7 LS checksum'

wfOspfLsdbAdvLen.name: wfOspfLsdbAdvLen
wfOspfLsdbAdvLen.description: 'The length of entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Advertisements'

wfOspfAreaRangeTable.name: wfOspfAreaRangeTable
wfOspfAreaRangeTable.description: 'A range if IP addresses specified by an IP address/IP network mask pair. For example, class B address range of X.X.X.X with a network mask of 255.255.0.0 includes all IP addresses from X.X.0.0 to X.X.255.255' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfAreaRangeDelete.name: wfOspfAreaRangeDelete
wfOspfAreaRangeDelete.description: This value determines if an Area Range has been configured for the OSPF router.

wfOspfAreaRangeDisable.name: wfOspfAreaRangeDisable
wfOspfAreaRangeDisable.description: 'This variable displays the status of the entry. Setting it to 'DISBALED' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.'

wfOspfAreaRangeState.name: wfOspfAreaRangeState
wfOspfAreaRangeState.description: The state of the OSPF Area Range.

wfOspfAreaRangeAreaID.name: wfOspfAreaRangeAreaID
wfOspfAreaRangeAreaID.description: 'The Area the Address Range is to be found within.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfAreaRangeNet.name: wfOspfAreaRangeNet
wfOspfAreaRangeNet.description: 'The IP Address of the Net or Subnet indicated by the range.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfAreaRangeMask.name: wfOspfAreaRangeMask
wfOspfAreaRangeMask.description: 'The Subnet Mask that pertains to the Net or Subnet.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters'

wfOspfIfTable.name: wfOspfIfTable
wfOspfIfTable.description: -- OSPF Interface Table -- The OSPF Interface Table augments the ifTable with OSPF -- specific information. 'The OSPF Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of OSPF.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters'

wfOspfIfEntry.name: wfOspfIfEntry
wfOspfIfEntry.description: 'The OSPF Interface Entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of OSPF.'

wfOspfIfDelete.name: wfOspfIfDelete
wfOspfIfDelete.description: This variable determines in an OSPF Interface has been configured on the router.

wfOspfIfDisable.name: wfOspfIfDisable
wfOspfIfDisable.description: 'The OSPF interface's administrative status. The value 'enabled' denotes that neighbor relationships may be formed on the interface, and the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPF.'

wfOspfIfState.name: wfOspfIfState
wfOspfIfState.description: 'The OSPF Interface State.' down (1), loopback (2), waiting (3), pointToPoint (4), designatedRouter (5), backupDesignatedRouter (6), otherDesignatedRouter (7)

wfOspfIfIpAddress.name: wfOspfIfIpAddress
wfOspfIfIpAddress.description: 'The IP address of this OSPF interface.'

wfOspfAddressLessIf.name: wfOspfAddressLessIf
wfOspfAddressLessIf.description: 'For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.'

wfOspfIfAreaId.name: wfOspfIfAreaId
wfOspfIfAreaId.description: 'A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.' default { '00000000'H } -- 0.0.0.0

wfOspfIfType.name: wfOspfIfType
wfOspfIfType.description: 'The OSPF interface type. By way of a default, this field may be intuited from the corresponding value of ifType. Broadcast LANs, such as Ethernet and IEEE 802.5, take the value 'broadcast', X.25, Frame Relay, and similar technologies take the value 'nbma', and links that are definitively point to point take the value 'pointToPoint'.' broadcast (1), nbma (2), pointToPoint (3)

wfOspfIfRtrPriority.name: wfOspfIfRtrPriority
wfOspfIfRtrPriority.description: 'The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their router id as a tie breaker.'

wfOspfIfTransitDelay.name: wfOspfIfTransitDelay
wfOspfIfTransitDelay.description: 'The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.'

wfOspfIfRetransInterval.name: wfOspfIfRetransInterval
wfOspfIfRetransInterval.description: 'The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets.'

wfOspfIfHelloInterval.name: wfOspfIfHelloInterval
wfOspfIfHelloInterval.description: 'The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.'

wfOspfIfRtrDeadInterval.name: wfOspfIfRtrDeadInterval
wfOspfIfRtrDeadInterval.description: 'The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.'

wfOspfIfPollInterval.name: wfOspfIfPollInterval
wfOspfIfPollInterval.description: 'The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non-broadcast multi- access neighbor.'

wfOspfIfDesignatedRouter.name: wfOspfIfDesignatedRouter
wfOspfIfDesignatedRouter.description: 'The IP Address of the Designated Router.' default { '00000000'H } -- 0.0.0.0

wfOspfIfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: wfOspfIfBackupDesignatedRouter
wfOspfIfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: 'The IP Address of the Backup Designated Router.' default { '00000000'H } -- 0.0.0.0

wfOspfIfMetricCost.name: wfOspfIfMetricCost
wfOspfIfMetricCost.description: 'The cost of using this type of service on this interface. The default value of the TOS 0 Metric is 10^8 / ifSpeed. The value FFFF is distinguished to mean 'no route via this TOS'.'

wfOspfIfAuthKey.name: wfOspfIfAuthKey
wfOspfIfAuthKey.description: 'The Authentication Key. If the Area's Authorization Type is simplePassword, and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, ospfIfAuthKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.' default { '0000000000000000'H } -- 0.0.0.0.0.0.0.0 REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure'

wfOspfIfTxHellos.name: wfOspfIfTxHellos
wfOspfIfTxHellos.description: Number of OSPF Hello packets transmitted.

wfOspfIfTxDBDescripts.name: wfOspfIfTxDBDescripts
wfOspfIfTxDBDescripts.description: Number of OSPF DataBase Description packets transmitted.

wfOspfIfTxLinkStateReqs.name: wfOspfIfTxLinkStateReqs
wfOspfIfTxLinkStateReqs.description: Number of OSPF Link State Request packets transmitted.

wfOspfIfTxLinkStateUpds.name: wfOspfIfTxLinkStateUpds
wfOspfIfTxLinkStateUpds.description: Number of OSPF Link State Update packets transmitted.

wfOspfIfTxLinkStateAcks.name: wfOspfIfTxLinkStateAcks
wfOspfIfTxLinkStateAcks.description: Number of OSPF Link States Acknowledgements transmitted.

wfOspfIfRxHellos.name: wfOspfIfRxHellos
wfOspfIfRxHellos.description: Number of OSPF Hello packets received.

wfOspfIfRxDBDescripts.name: wfOspfIfRxDBDescripts
wfOspfIfRxDBDescripts.description: Number of OSPF DataBase Description packets received.

wfOspfIfRxLinkStateReqs.name: wfOspfIfRxLinkStateReqs
wfOspfIfRxLinkStateReqs.description: Number of OSPF Link State Requests received.

wfOspfIfRxLinkStateUpds.name: wfOspfIfRxLinkStateUpds
wfOspfIfRxLinkStateUpds.description: Number of OSPF Link State Updates received.

wfOspfIfRxLinkStateAcks.name: wfOspfIfRxLinkStateAcks
wfOspfIfRxLinkStateAcks.description: Number of OSPF Link State Acknowledgements received.

wfOspfIfDrops.name: wfOspfIfDrops
wfOspfIfDrops.description: Number of OSPF packets dropped because of invalid information in the packet.

wfOspfVirtIfTable.name: wfOspfVirtIfTable
wfOspfVirtIfTable.description: -- OSPF Virtual Interface Table -- The Virtual Interface Table describes the virtual -- links that the OSPF Process is configured to -- carry on. 'Information about this router's virtual interfaces.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters'

wfOspfVirtIfDisable.name: wfOspfVirtIfDisable
wfOspfVirtIfDisable.description: 'This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.'

wfOspfVirtIfState.name: wfOspfVirtIfState
wfOspfVirtIfState.description: 'OSPF virtual interface states.' down (1), -- these use the same encoding pointToPoint (4) -- as the ospfIfTable

wfOspfVirtIfAreaID.name: wfOspfVirtIfAreaID
wfOspfVirtIfAreaID.description: 'The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0'

wfOspfVirtIfNeighbor.name: wfOspfVirtIfNeighbor
wfOspfVirtIfNeighbor.description: 'The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.'

wfOspfVirtIfTransitDelay.name: wfOspfVirtIfTransitDelay
wfOspfVirtIfTransitDelay.description: 'The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.'

wfOspfVirtIfRetransInterval.name: wfOspfVirtIfRetransInterval
wfOspfVirtIfRetransInterval.description: 'The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round-trip time.'

wfOspfVirtIfHelloInterval.name: wfOspfVirtIfHelloInterval
wfOspfVirtIfHelloInterval.description: 'The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.'

wfOspfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: wfOspfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval
wfOspfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: 'The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.'

wfOspfVirtIfAuthKey.name: wfOspfVirtIfAuthKey
wfOspfVirtIfAuthKey.description: 'If Authentication Type is simplePassword, the device will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, ospfVifAuthKey always returns a string of length zero.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure'

wfOspfVirtIfTxHellos.name: wfOspfVirtIfTxHellos
wfOspfVirtIfTxHellos.description: Number of OSPF Hello packets transmitted on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfTxDBDescripts.name: wfOspfVirtIfTxDBDescripts
wfOspfVirtIfTxDBDescripts.description: Number of OSPF DataBase Description packets transmitted on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateReqs.name: wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateReqs
wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateReqs.description: Number of OSPF Link State Request packets transmitted on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateUpds.name: wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateUpds
wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateUpds.description: Number of OSPF Link State Update packets transmitted on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateAcks.name: wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateAcks
wfOspfVirtIfTxLinkStateAcks.description: Number of OSPF Link State Acknowledgement packets transmitted on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfRxHellos.name: wfOspfVirtIfRxHellos
wfOspfVirtIfRxHellos.description: Number of OSPF Hello packets received on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfRxDBDescripts.name: wfOspfVirtIfRxDBDescripts
wfOspfVirtIfRxDBDescripts.description: Number of OSPF DataBase Description packets received on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateReqs.name: wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateReqs
wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateReqs.description: Number of OSPF Link State Request packets recieved on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateUpds.name: wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateUpds
wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateUpds.description: Number of OSPF Link State Update packets received on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateAcks.name: wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateAcks
wfOspfVirtIfRxLinkStateAcks.description: Number of OSPF Link State Acknowledgement packets received on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfVirtIfDrops.name: wfOspfVirtIfDrops
wfOspfVirtIfDrops.description: Number of OSPF packets dropped on Virtual Interfaces.

wfOspfNbrTable.name: wfOspfNbrTable
wfOspfNbrTable.description: -- OSPF Neighbor Table -- The OSPF Neighbor Table describes all neighbors in -- the locality of the subject router. 'A table of non-virtual neighbor information.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure'

wfOspfNbrEntry.name: wfOspfNbrEntry
wfOspfNbrEntry.description: 'The information regarding a single neighbor.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure'

wfOspfNbrDelete.name: wfOspfNbrDelete
wfOspfNbrDelete.description: This variable indicates the existence of a static OSPF neighbor.

wfOspfNbrDisable.name: wfOspfNbrDisable
wfOspfNbrDisable.description: 'This variable displays the status of the entry. Setting it to 'DISABLED' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.'

wfOspfNbrState.name: wfOspfNbrState
wfOspfNbrState.description: 'The State of the relationship with this Neighbor.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 10.1 Neighbor States' down (1), attempt (2), init (3), twoWay (4), exchangeStart (5), exchange (6), loading (7), full (8)

wfOspfNbrIfAddr.name: wfOspfNbrIfAddr
wfOspfNbrIfAddr.description: 'The Interface IP address for this neighbor.'

wfOspfNbrAddressLessIndex.name: wfOspfNbrAddressLessIndex
wfOspfNbrAddressLessIndex.description: ' On an interface having an IP Address, zero. On addressless interfaces, the corresponding value of ifIndex in the Internet Standard MIB. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.'

wfOspfNbrRtrId.name: wfOspfNbrRtrId
wfOspfNbrRtrId.description: 'A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAddress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.' default { '00000000'H } -- 0.0.0.0

wfOspfNbrOptions.name: wfOspfNbrOptions
wfOspfNbrOptions.description: 'A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Bit 0, if set, indicates that the area accepts and operates on external information; if zero, it is a stub area. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.2 Options'

wfOspfNbrPriority.name: wfOspfNbrPriority
wfOspfNbrPriority.description: 'The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.'

wfOspfNbrEvents.name: wfOspfNbrEvents
wfOspfNbrEvents.description: 'The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.'

wfOspfNbrLSRetransQLen.name: wfOspfNbrLSRetransQLen
wfOspfNbrLSRetransQLen.description: 'The current length of the retransmission queue.'

wfOspfVirtNbrTable.name: wfOspfVirtNbrTable
wfOspfVirtNbrTable.description: -- WFOSPF Virtual Neighbor Table -- This table describes all virtual neighbors. -- Since Virtual Links are configured in the -- virtual interface table, this table is read-only. 'A table of virtual neighbor information.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, '

wfOspfVirtNbrRtrId.name: wfOspfVirtNbrRtrId
wfOspfVirtNbrRtrId.description: 'A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.'

wfOspfVirtNbrIpAddr.name: wfOspfVirtNbrIpAddr
wfOspfVirtNbrIpAddr.description: 'The IP address this Virtual Neighbor is using.'

wfOspfVirtNbrOptions.name: wfOspfVirtNbrOptions
wfOspfVirtNbrOptions.description: 'A bit map corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Thus, Bit 1, if set, indicates that the neighbor supports Type of Service Routing; if zero, no metrics other than TOS 0 are in use by the neighbor.'

wfOspfVirtNbrState.name: wfOspfVirtNbrState
wfOspfVirtNbrState.description: 'The state of the Virtual Neighbor Relationship.' down (1), attempt (2), init (3), twoWay (4), exchangeStart (5), exchange (6), loading (7), full (8)

wfOspfVirtNbrEvents.name: wfOspfVirtNbrEvents
wfOspfVirtNbrEvents.description: 'The number of times this virtual link has changed its state, or an error has occurred.'

wfOspfVirtNbrLSRetransQLen.name: wfOspfVirtNbrLSRetransQLen
wfOspfVirtNbrLSRetransQLen.description: 'The current length of the retransmission queue.'

wfOspfDynNbrTable.name: wfOspfDynNbrTable
wfOspfDynNbrTable.description: -- OSPF Dynamic Neighbor Table -- The OSPF Dynamic Neighbor Table describes all neighbors in -- the locality of the subject router learned during operation. 'A table of non-virtual neighbor information.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure'

wfOspfDynNbrEntry.name: wfOspfDynNbrEntry
wfOspfDynNbrEntry.description: 'The information regarding a single neighbor.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure'

wfOspfDynNbrState.name: wfOspfDynNbrState
wfOspfDynNbrState.description: 'The State of the relationship with this Neighbor.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 10.1 Neighbor States' down (1), attempt (2), init (3), twoWay (4), exchangeStart (5), exchange (6), loading (7), full (8)

wfOspfDynNbrIfAddr.name: wfOspfDynNbrIfAddr
wfOspfDynNbrIfAddr.description: 'The Interface IP address for this neighbor.'

wfOspfDynNbrAddressLessIndex.name: wfOspfDynNbrAddressLessIndex
wfOspfDynNbrAddressLessIndex.description: ' On an interface having an IP Address, zero. On addressless interfaces, the corresponding value of ifIndex in the Internet Standard MIB. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.'

wfOspfDynNbrRtrId.name: wfOspfDynNbrRtrId
wfOspfDynNbrRtrId.description: 'A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAddress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.' default { '00000000'H } -- 0.0.0.0

wfOspfDynNbrOptions.name: wfOspfDynNbrOptions
wfOspfDynNbrOptions.description: 'A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Bit 0, if set, indicates that the area accepts and operates on external information; if zero, it is a stub area. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric.' REFERENCE 'OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.2 Options'

wfOspfDynNbrPriority.name: wfOspfDynNbrPriority
wfOspfDynNbrPriority.description: 'The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.'

wfOspfDynNbrEvents.name: wfOspfDynNbrEvents
wfOspfDynNbrEvents.description: 'The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.'

wfOspfDynNbrLSRetransQLen.name: wfOspfDynNbrLSRetransQLen
wfOspfDynNbrLSRetransQLen.description: 'The current length of the retransmission queue.'

wfIpRfRipImportTable.name: wfIpRfRipImportTable
wfIpRfRipImportTable.description: The list of Rip Import Route Filter Rules in IP

wfIpRfRipImportEntry.name: wfIpRfRipImportEntry
wfIpRfRipImportEntry.description: An entry in the Rip Import Rule Table

wfBrSrIpExplorerAddr.description: The IP address of this encapsulation peer.

wfBrSrIpEncapsTable.description: A table that contains information about IP Encapsulation ring-to-IP Address mappings. This information is used to make the 'next ring' IP Address decision. inst = wfBrSrIpEncapsRing

wfBrSrTrafficFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfBrSrTrafficFilterStatus.description: Defines the current status of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfBrSrTrafficFilterCircuit.description: The ID of the Bridge Circuit to which the filter is applied.

wfBrSrEsRifCircuit.description: The circuit on which this entry was learned

wfBrSrEsRifRoute.name: wfBrSrEsRifRoute

wfSyncEntry.description: An entry in the SYNC table

wfSyncConnector.description: Instance ID Connector, filled in by driver

wfSyncCct.description: CCT number for this line instance

wfSyncBoflTmo.description: breath of life timeout in seconds

wfSyncMtu.description: MTU parameter, this is buffer size for SYNC media, fixed

wfSyncMadr.name: wfSyncMadr
wfSyncMadr.description: Line MAC address, fixed - line driver fills in from the 48 bit address stored in the serial number prom for this connector.

wfSyncPromiscuous.name: wfSyncPromiscuous
wfSyncPromiscuous.description: The promiscuous parameter allows address filtering based on the local and remote addresses. When enabled, all frames are received, disabled indicates only frames destined for this local address are received

wfSyncXid.name: wfSyncXid
wfSyncXid.description: XID enable/disable parameter. This parameter is used to enable or disable transmission/reception of Test XID frames.

wfSyncClkSource.name: wfSyncClkSource
wfSyncClkSource.description: Tx/Rx clock source is either internally or external generated.

wfSyncClkSpeed.name: wfSyncClkSpeed
wfSyncClkSpeed.description: Tx/Rx clock speed. This speed selection is valid only when the internal clock speed parameter has been selected.

wfSyncSignalMode.name: wfSyncSignalMode
wfSyncSignalMode.description: The signal mode parameter indicates the line paramter balanced or unbalanced.

wfSyncRtsEnable.name: wfSyncRtsEnable
wfSyncRtsEnable.description: The RTS parameter enables/disables detection of RTS signals on the interface. Normal default mode is running without RTS enabled.

wfSyncBurstCount.name: wfSyncBurstCount
wfSyncBurstCount.description: Allows single or multiple DMA burst cycles. When enabled the chip performs 8 word burst's. Single word cycles are performed when disabled

wfSyncService.name: wfSyncService
wfSyncService.description: Service type for this circuit. Transparent is raw HDLC mode, LLC1 will prefix the HDLC address and control fields to the frame. The LLC2 service provides the LAPB protocol service.

wfSyncRetryCount.name: wfSyncRetryCount
wfSyncRetryCount.description: The Retry count parameter indicates the number of retransmission attempts which will be tried per frame before a line is determined to be down. The retry count is max attempts following expiration of the T1 timer. This parameter is equal to the N2 counter in ICB.

wfSyncLinkIdleTimer.name: wfSyncLinkIdleTimer
wfSyncLinkIdleTimer.description: The link idle parameter is the number of seconds before a line has been determined to be idle. An idle line is considered disconnectd This value is expressed in seconds.

wfSyncRetryTimer.name: wfSyncRetryTimer
wfSyncRetryTimer.description: The Retry Timer parameter indicates the timeout in seconds for a response to be heard form the link. Link control frames are sent at the expiration of this timer value. The frames will be resent up to retry count (N2) at which time the link will be disconnected.

wfSyncExtendedAddress.name: wfSyncExtendedAddress
wfSyncExtendedAddress.description: This parameter controls length determination of the address field. When this parameter is enabled, the first bit of the address field be tested to determine the length of address field in octets.

wfSyncExtendedAddressForce.name: wfSyncExtendedAddressForce
wfSyncExtendedAddressForce.description: When this parameter is enabled, the receiver will assume that all address fields are 2 octets in length regardless of the first two bits of the control field. Usefull only in Transparent Mode.

wfSyncExtendedControl.name: wfSyncExtendedControl
wfSyncExtendedControl.description: This parameter allows the control fields of all S and I frames to become 2 octets in length instead of one. Numbering of all I frame become modulo 128 instead of modulo 8. The control field of U frames remains one octet in length.

wfSyncExtendedControlForce.name: wfSyncExtendedControlForce
wfSyncExtendedControlForce.description: This parameter when enabled will force all control fields to become two octets in length regardless the first two bits in the control field. Usefull only in Transparent Mode. (LLC1)

wfSyncConnectAttempts.name: wfSyncConnectAttempts
wfSyncConnectAttempts.description: This parameter controls the number of connection attempts which will be made during a LAPB connection request. This parameter is applicable only during LLC2 service.

wfSyncWindowSizeTx.name: wfSyncWindowSizeTx
wfSyncWindowSizeTx.description: The window size parameter controls the number of I frames which may be transmitted without acknowledgement. Non EXTC mode.

wfSyncWindowSizeTxExtc.name: wfSyncWindowSizeTxExtc
wfSyncWindowSizeTxExtc.description: The window size parameter controls the number of I frames which may be transmitted without acknowledgement in EXTC mode.

wfSyncMinFrameSpace.name: wfSyncMinFrameSpace
wfSyncMinFrameSpace.description: The minimum frame spacing parameter defines the number of flags that are transmitted between adjacent frames.

wfSyncLocalAddress.name: wfSyncLocalAddress
wfSyncLocalAddress.description: The local address parameter contains the DTE,DCE or EXPLICIT value expressed as a single octet. It may be extended to 2 octets if EXTA has been set.

wfSyncRemoteAddress.name: wfSyncRemoteAddress
wfSyncRemoteAddress.description: The remote address parameter contains the DTE,DCE or EXPLICIT value expressed as a single octet. It may be extended to 2 octets if EXTA has been set.

wfSyncPassThruLocalMadr.name: wfSyncPassThruLocalMadr
wfSyncPassThruLocalMadr.description: 48 bit MAC address of Local end of Sync Passthru circuit

wfSyncPassThruRemoteMadr.name: wfSyncPassThruRemoteMadr
wfSyncPassThruRemoteMadr.description: 48 bit MAC address of Remote end of Sync Passthru circuit

wfSyncWanProtocol.name: wfSyncWanProtocol
wfSyncWanProtocol.description: WAN protocol selection is provided via this parameter. The supported protocols can be selected per interface.

wfSyncCrcSize.name: wfSyncCrcSize
wfSyncCrcSize.description: CRC size parameter, 16 bit standard CCITT or extended 32 bit CRC

wfSyncRxOctets.name: wfSyncRxOctets
wfSyncRxOctets.description: Number of octets received without error

wfSyncRxFrames.name: wfSyncRxFrames
wfSyncRxFrames.description: Number of frames received without error

wfSyncTxOctets.name: wfSyncTxOctets
wfSyncTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted without error

wfSyncTxFrames.name: wfSyncTxFrames
wfSyncTxFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted without error

wfSyncLackRescRx.name: wfSyncLackRescRx
wfSyncLackRescRx.description: Number of Rx frames dropped due to lack of buffer resources

wfSyncLackRescTx.name: wfSyncLackRescTx
wfSyncLackRescTx.description: Number of Tx frames dropped due to lack of buffer resources

wfSyncUnderFlowTx.name: wfSyncUnderFlowTx
wfSyncUnderFlowTx.description: Number of transmission underflows, device FIFO went empty before next DMA request was granted.

wfSyncRejectsTx.name: wfSyncRejectsTx
wfSyncRejectsTx.description: Number of reject frames which were transmitted

wfSyncRejectsRx.name: wfSyncRejectsRx
wfSyncRejectsRx.description: Number of reject frames which were received

wfSyncOverFlowRx.name: wfSyncOverFlowRx
wfSyncOverFlowRx.description: Number of receive overflows, device FIFO overflowed before next DMA cycle granted. No buffer resources available.

wfSyncFramesIncompRx.name: wfSyncFramesIncompRx
wfSyncFramesIncompRx.description: Number of frames which were incompletely received. These are frames which may have resulted from FRMRR errors.

wfSyncBadFramesRx.name: wfSyncBadFramesRx
wfSyncBadFramesRx.description: Number of bad receive frames, caused by FCS errors or non octet aligned.

wfSyncT1Timeouts.name: wfSyncT1Timeouts
wfSyncT1Timeouts.description: Number of T1 timeout's detected. The T1 timer is the link retransmission timer. Link control frames will be retransmitted when T1 expires. This is a count of the number of timeouts.

wfSyncMemoryErrors.name: wfSyncMemoryErrors
wfSyncMemoryErrors.description: Number of memory access errors detected. A MERR is the expiration of a DMA cycle without the bus being granted within 26us.

wfSyncMediaType.name: wfSyncMediaType
wfSyncMediaType.description: Media type selection is provided via this parameter

wfSysName.name: wfSysName
wfSysName.description: Node's fully qualified domain name or administratively assigned name

wfSysServices.name: wfSysServices
wfSysServices.description: A sum of numbers indicating the set of services the entity offers. For each layer L, add 2**(L - 1). Example: 78 = Layers 2,3,4, and 7.

wfSysGmtOffset.name: wfSysGmtOffset
wfSysGmtOffset.description: The positive or negative offset from Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). This effectively describes the time zone.

wfSysMibVersion.name: wfSysMibVersion
wfSysMibVersion.description: The version of the private management information base currently being used by the system software. Format is: xV.RR

wfT1FrameType.description: Frame Type - differentiates between two tarrifed framing formats D4 and ESF.

wfT1LineBuildout.description: Line Buildout - Approximate length of cable

wfT1B8ZSSupport.description: B8ZS Support - Enables or disables Binary 8 zeros suppression

wfT1ClockMode.description: Clock Mode - Specifies the source of the T1 transmit clock

wfT1MiniDacs.description: MiniDacs Configuration - assigns each T1 channel to a specific function

wfTftpCloseTimeOut.name: wfTftpCloseTimeOut
wfTftpCloseTimeOut.description: Retransmission time-out value for sender of final ACK (seconds)

wfTiRuiState.description: The state of the ti rui command processor. Idle is normal state. Busy indicates a command is being processed.

wfTiRuiResult.description: The result of the Ti command requst

wfTiRuiOutResults.description: Total number of command requests that processed without error

wfTiRuiOutResultsErr.description: Total number of command requests that could not be processed because of errors

wfTokenRingEntry.description: An entry in the token table

wfTokenRingState.description: line driver state variable, Not Present, Init, Down, Up

wfTokenRingConnector.description: instance ID Connector, filled in by driver

wfTokenRingCct.name: wfTokenRingCct
wfTokenRingCct.description: cct number for this line instance, configuration required

wfTokenRingMtu.name: wfTokenRingMtu
wfTokenRingMtu.description: mtu parameter, fixed. This mtu of 4568 allows a type 3 Source Route Frame (info=4472) to be IP encapsulated over Token Ring. The components are: AC_FC (2) + SNAP (12+8) + SNAP_IP (12+8+20) + SR (12+18) + TYPE3_INFO (4472) + FCS (4) --------------------- total 4568 bytes

wfTokenRingMadr.name: wfTokenRingMadr
wfTokenRingMadr.description: line MAC address, line driver fills in the currently used 48 bit MAC address.

wfTokenRingCfgMadr.name: wfTokenRingCfgMadr
wfTokenRingCfgMadr.description: Configured line MAC address. Only used if wfTokenRingMadrSelect is set appropriately.

wfTokenRingMadrSelect.name: wfTokenRingMadrSelect
wfTokenRingMadrSelect.description: Selector determines which MAC address the interface will use.

wfTokenRingSpeed.name: wfTokenRingSpeed
wfTokenRingSpeed.description: Token Ring speed parameter - 4 and 16 Mbps are only valid values

wfTokenRingEarlyTokenRelease.name: wfTokenRingEarlyTokenRelease
wfTokenRingEarlyTokenRelease.description: Early Token Release parameter, only valid with 16Mbps

wfTokenRingStatus.name: wfTokenRingStatus
wfTokenRingStatus.description: The current interface status. This attribute is only valid when the wfTokenRingOpenState attribute is set to OPENED. The attribute's value is a sum of values, one for each currently applicable condition (ie, bit positions indicate active conditions). Occurrences of each condition are separately counted and the counts are included in this MIB as attributes wfTokenRingSignalLosses through wfTokenRingRingRecoveries. The following values are defined: 32768 = Signal Losses 16384 = Hard Errors 8192 = Soft Errors 4096 = Transmit Beacons 2048 = Lobe Wire Faults 1024 = Auto-Removal Errors 256 = Remove Received 128 = Counter Overflows 64 = Single Stations 32 = Ring Recoveries This attribute is the most recent sum of these conditions. More information on each condition is include in the descriptions of the individual counter attributes.

wfTokenRingOpenState.name: wfTokenRingOpenState
wfTokenRingOpenState.description: The current interface state with respect to entering or leaving the ring.

wfTokenRingOpenStatus.name: wfTokenRingOpenStatus
wfTokenRingOpenStatus.description: Indicates the success, or the reason for failure, of the station's most recent attempt to enter the ring.

wfTokenRingUpStream.name: wfTokenRingUpStream
wfTokenRingUpStream.description: MAC address of Up Stream neighbor. Only valid when 'opened'.

wfTokenRingRxOctets.name: wfTokenRingRxOctets
wfTokenRingRxOctets.description: Number of octets received without error.

wfTokenRingRxFrames.name: wfTokenRingRxFrames
wfTokenRingRxFrames.description: Number of frames received without error.

wfTokenRingTxOctets.name: wfTokenRingTxOctets
wfTokenRingTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted without error.

wfTokenRingTxFrames.name: wfTokenRingTxFrames
wfTokenRingTxFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted without error.

wfTokenRingInDiscards.name: wfTokenRingInDiscards
wfTokenRingInDiscards.description: Number of error-free inbound packets discarded. Usually due to lack of memory resources. This is equivalent to wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors.

wfTokenRingInErrors.name: wfTokenRingInErrors
wfTokenRingInErrors.description: Number of inbound packets not delivered to higher-layer protocol due to errors. The sum of wfTokenRingLineErrors and wfTokenRingBurstErrors.

wfTokenRingOutDiscards.name: wfTokenRingOutDiscards
wfTokenRingOutDiscards.description: Number of error-free outbound packets discarded. Usually due to lack of transmission bandwidth. This is equivalent to wfTokenRingTxClipFrames.

wfTokenRingOutErrors.name: wfTokenRingOutErrors
wfTokenRingOutErrors.description: Number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. This is equivalent to wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors.

wfTokenRingTxClipFrames.name: wfTokenRingTxClipFrames
wfTokenRingTxClipFrames.description: Number of frames clipped in driver's transmit routine due to transmit congestion.

wfTokenRingRxReplenMisses.name: wfTokenRingRxReplenMisses
wfTokenRingRxReplenMisses.description: Number of packet buffer misses while attempting to replenish driver receive ring.

wfTokenRingSignalLosses.name: wfTokenRingSignalLosses
wfTokenRingSignalLosses.description: Number of ring signal losses detected.

wfTokenRingHardErrors.name: wfTokenRingHardErrors
wfTokenRingHardErrors.description: Number of events causing the adapter to transmit or receive beacon MAC frames.

wfTokenRingSoftErrors.name: wfTokenRingSoftErrors
wfTokenRingSoftErrors.description: Number of soft errors. Corresponds to the number of Report Error MAC frames transmitted by this station.

wfTokenRingTransmitBeacons.name: wfTokenRingTransmitBeacons
wfTokenRingTransmitBeacons.description: Number of events causing the adapter to transmit beacon frames.

wfTokenRingLobeWireFaults.name: wfTokenRingLobeWireFaults
wfTokenRingLobeWireFaults.description: Number of opens or shorts (cable faults) between the adapter and the MAU.

wfTokenRingAutoRemovalErrors.name: wfTokenRingAutoRemovalErrors
wfTokenRingAutoRemovalErrors.description: Number of lobe wrap test failures during beacon auto_removal process.

wfTokenRingRequestRemoves.name: wfTokenRingRequestRemoves
wfTokenRingRequestRemoves.description: Number of Remove Ring Station MAC frames received. Each frame causes this station to leave the ring.

wfTokenRingCounterOverflows.name: wfTokenRingCounterOverflows
wfTokenRingCounterOverflows.description: Number of adapter error counter overflows.

wfTokenRingSingleStations.name: wfTokenRingSingleStations
wfTokenRingSingleStations.description: Number of ring status change interrupts while adapter is only station on the ring.

wfTokenRingRingRecoveries.name: wfTokenRingRingRecoveries
wfTokenRingRingRecoveries.description: Number of claim token MAC frames (ring recoveries) observed on the ring.

wfTokenRingAdapterChecks.name: wfTokenRingAdapterChecks
wfTokenRingAdapterChecks.description: Number of internal adapter errors that result in adapter crashes.

wfTokenRingFirstAdapterCheckCode.name: wfTokenRingFirstAdapterCheckCode
wfTokenRingFirstAdapterCheckCode.description: Adapter Check Code of first occurrence.

wfTokenRingLastAdapterCheckCode.name: wfTokenRingLastAdapterCheckCode
wfTokenRingLastAdapterCheckCode.description: Adapter Check Code of most recent (last) occurrence.

wfTokenRingLineErrors.name: wfTokenRingLineErrors
wfTokenRingLineErrors.description: Number of frames copied or repeated by this station with bad format or an FCS error.

wfTokenRingBurstErrors.name: wfTokenRingBurstErrors
wfTokenRingBurstErrors.description: Number of errored frames with no transition for 5 1/2 bit times.

wfTokenRingAriFciErrors.name: wfTokenRingAriFciErrors
wfTokenRingAriFciErrors.description: Number of occurrences of this station receiving both an AMP MAC frame and a SMP MAC frame with the a & c bits clear or more than one SMP MAC frame with the a & c bits clear without an intervening AMP MAC frame. This condition indicates that the up-stream neighbor is unable to set the a & c bits in a frame that it has copied.

wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors.name: wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors
wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors.description: Number of frames being stripped which are missing their tails.

wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors.name: wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors
wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors.description: Number of frames dropped due to receive congestion.

wfTokenRingFrameCopiedErrors.name: wfTokenRingFrameCopiedErrors
wfTokenRingFrameCopiedErrors.description: Number of specifically addressed frames for this station that had their a & c bits previously set.

wfTokenRingTokenErrors.name: wfTokenRingTokenErrors
wfTokenRingTokenErrors.description: Number of token protocol errors. Only relevant when this station is the active monitor.

wfTokenRingDmaBusErrors.name: wfTokenRingDmaBusErrors
wfTokenRingDmaBusErrors.description: Number of bus errors during DMA that do not exceed threshold.

wfTokenRingDmaParityErrors.name: wfTokenRingDmaParityErrors
wfTokenRingDmaParityErrors.description: Number of parity errors during DMA that do not exceed threshold.

wfTokenRingSrbNotFreeCmdAborts.name: wfTokenRingSrbNotFreeCmdAborts
wfTokenRingSrbNotFreeCmdAborts.description: Number of host to adapter commands aborted because of in-completed in process commands.

wfTokenRingRxProcessings.name: wfTokenRingRxProcessings
wfTokenRingRxProcessings.description: Number of processings of received frames (similar to RINT).

wfTokenRingTxProcessings.name: wfTokenRingTxProcessings
wfTokenRingTxProcessings.description: Number of processings of frames for transmit.

wfTokenRingTxCmplProcessings.name: wfTokenRingTxCmplProcessings
wfTokenRingTxCmplProcessings.description: Number of processings of transmitted frames (similar to TINT).

wfTokenRingRxTimeouts.name: wfTokenRingRxTimeouts
wfTokenRingRxTimeouts.description: Number of re-initializations due to receiver time-outs.

wfTokenRingCmdTimeouts.name: wfTokenRingCmdTimeouts
wfTokenRingCmdTimeouts.description: Number of re-initializations due to command time-outs.

wfTokenRingRxHostIntErrors.name: wfTokenRingRxHostIntErrors
wfTokenRingRxHostIntErrors.description: Number of re-initializations due to receive host interface errors.
